c to the ordinal `o`, living in the same universe. This is\ndefined through the axiom of choice.\n\nUse this over `Iio o` only when it is paramount to have a `Type u` rather than a `Type (u + 1)`,\nand convert using\n\n```\nOrdinal.ToType.mk : Iio o → o.ToType\nOrdinal.ToType.toOrd : o.ToType → Iio o\n```\n","docLink":"./Mathlib/SetTheory/Ordinal/Basic.html#Ordinal.toType","kind":"def","line":122,"name":"Ordinal.toType","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/SetTheory/Ordinal/Basic.lean#L122-L123"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/SetTheory/Ordinal/Basic.html#Ordinal.ToType\"><span class=\"name\">Ordinal</span>.<span class=\"name\">ToType</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">o</span> : <a href=\"./Mathlib/SetTheory/Ordinal/Basic.html#Ordinal\">Ordinal.{u}</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u</div></div>","info":{"doc":"A \"canonical\" type order-isomorphic to the ordinal `o`, living in the same universe. This is\ndefined through the axiom of choice.\n\nUse this over `Iio o` only when it is paramount to have a `Type u` rather than a `Type (u + 1)`,\nand convert using\n\n```\nOrdinal.ToType.mk : Iio o → o.ToType\nOrdinal.ToType.toOrd : o.ToType → Iio o\n```\n","docLink":"./Mathlib/SetTheory/Ordinal/Basic.html#Ordinal.ToType","kind":"def","line":108,"name":"Ordinal.ToType","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/SetTheory/Ordinal/Basic.lean#L108-L120"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/SetTheory/Ordinal/Basic.html#Ordinal\"><span class=\"name\">Ordinal</span><